(3, 'instructor', 'A personal trainer is a fitness professional involved in exercise prescription and instruction. They motivate clients by setting goals and providing feedback and accountability to clients. Trainers also measure their client''s strengths and weaknesses with fitness assessments. These fitness assessments may also be performed before and after an exercise program to measure their client''s improvements in physical fitness.\r\n\r\nThey may also educate their clients in many other aspects of wellness besides exercise, including general health and nutrition guidelines. Qualified personal trainers recognize their own areas of expertise. If a trainer suspects that one of his or her clients has a medical condition that could prevent the client from safe participation in an exercise program, they must refer the client to the proper health professional for prior clearance.'),
(4, 'iotm', 'Every Month, our costumers vote our instructor, and the one who gets the highest number of votes can procalim himself\r\n"The Instructor of the Month"!\r\nWhat''s the deal with this? Nothing special but some glory on our special website page and some additional infos regarding\r\ntheir own life!'),
(5, 'error', 'The page you requested is not avaiable yet.<br><br>\r\nOur courses are so good that even our IT guys stop hiding behind their PCs and go exercising!');

